  pmid         = {36324567},
  keywords     = {venous compression syndromes, May Thurner syndrome, Nutcracker syndrome, fatigue, orthostatic intolerance},
  research_stream = {may-thurner},
  certainty    = {0.70},
  note         = {Systematic review of 47 studies (2,481 patients). Distribution: MTS 72\%, Nutcracker 18\%, co-occurrence 10\%. Fatigue prevalence 28-47\% across syndromes. Orthostatic symptoms 34-58\% prevalence. SF-36 Physical Component Score 32.4 ± 8.1 (vs. population norm 50). Stenting improved fatigue in 68\% of symptomatic patients. Mean diagnostic delay 4.2 ± 3.6 years. Female predominance 3.2:1. Establishes fatigue and orthostatic symptoms as common features. Diagnostic delay parallels ME/CFS. Fatigue improvement after stenting suggests reversible component. Heterogeneous study designs.}
}

